      • startLogHandler

        public static final <T extends LogHandler> T startLogHandler(T h)
        Starts a log handler.

        This should be used like this: 

         LogHandler log = SkriptLogger.startLogHandler(new ...LogHandler());
 try {
        doSomethingThatLogsMessages();
        // do something with the logged messages
 } finally {
        log.stop();
 }
        Returns:
        The passed LogHandler
        See Also:
        startParseLogHandler(), startRetainingLog(), BlockingLogHandler, CountingLogHandler, ErrorDescLogHandler, FilteringLogHandler, RedirectingLogHandler
